<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Differential diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Scutellum only partly yellow pilose, black pilose anteriorly and medially. Tergite II-III extensively rufous to yellow pilose. Tergite IV dominantly black pilose, but sometimes with rufous or yellow pile medially or posteriorly. Hind trochanter not tuberculate in male.</paragraph>
